## ⚙️ Execution & Local Setup

### Prerequisites
* .NET SDK (v8.0 or higher)
* Node.js & Angular CLI (v18+)
* Docker Desktop (for backing services)

<details open>
<summary><strong>Step 1: Spin up Infrastructure</strong></summary>

Start PostgreSQL and Kafka using the provided compose file.
\`\`\`bash
docker-compose up -d
\`\`\`
</details>

<details open>
<summary><strong>Step 2: Start the Backend API</strong></summary>

Navigate to the API directory, apply migrations, and run.
\`\`\`bash
cd src/wallet.api
dotnet ef database update
dotnet run
\`\`\`
</details>

<details open>
<summary><strong>Step 3: Start the Angular Client</strong></summary>

Navigate to the UI directory and serve the application.
\`\`\`bash
cd src/web/wallet-ui
npm install
ng serve
\`\`\`
</details>

